I am running a task with >100000 dependency tasks (each of which has one dependency). It appears that when the scheduler is informed about all these dependencies in the `requires` method, the dependencies are generated very slowly. The log line `DEBUG: Asking scheduler for work` sits there for ~2 minutes before a worker starts running the next dependency. However, when dependencies are dynamically called for in the `run` method, the script moves much faster. Any idea what might be causing this slowdown?

